A little late now, but for reference:<br /><a href="http://www.midi.org/techspecs/electrispec.php" class="postlink">http://www.midi.org/techspecs/electrispec.php</a><br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />The MIDI IN connector is supposed to have the opto-isolator and no ground connection to pin 2 or to the shield for the express purpose of avoiding a ground loop.<br /></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sat Sep 21, 2013 11:24 pm</p><hr />
