<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10509&amp;p=118285#p118285"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">bazz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />What confused me is that, MIDI IN is a Port, not a cable.<br /><br />Perhaps they just did it this way to convey that the cable portion is grounded.<br /><br />So do I not need to worry about shielding once the cable plugs into the port and i build the circuit?<br /></div><br /><br />The outer metalic circular ring should be grounded, so that the outer sheild of the cable is grounded when connected to your port.  That's usually the large chassis like portion of your port, the big leads that fix it to the circuit board.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4832">infiniteneslives</a> — Thu Sep 19, 2013 10:47 am</p><hr />
