<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10509&amp;p=118274#p118274"><![CDATA[
<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Optoisolator_Pinout.svg">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Opto ... Pinout.svg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />There isn't a symbol for &quot;this signal is isolated&quot;, just the actual use of it.<br /><br />The MIDI OUT jack should be have its shield grounded, so that the cable's shield is grounded on the transmitting side. The receving side should have an optoisolator from current source (pin 4) to current sink (pin 5) and not be in any other way connected.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Wed Sep 18, 2013 11:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
